The paper deals with the problem of detecting an odd process among a group of Poisson point processes, which involves statistical inference and decision-making. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a likelihood ratio based sequential policy also suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the application of the results to a visual search experiment suggests a connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV).
